properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 18 at 3:44AM EST until January 20 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...South to southwest wind 15 to 25 knots with gusts up to
30 knots from late today into tonight. West to northwest wind 20
to 25 knots with gusts up to 30 knots on Sunday and Sunday
night. Seas 4 to 7 feet are expected.

* WHERE...The Atlantic coastal waters of New Jersey and Delaware.

* WHEN...From 4:00 PM this afternoon until 6:00 AM Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 6 AM EST MONDAY
